Chesapeake Asset Management, LLC










Managing Members Sherrill L. Blalock, CFA, Co-Founder and Managing Member since 1998.Prior to founding Chesapeake, Ms. Blalock was a General Partner at Delphi Asset Management, a General Partner of Weiss, Peck and Greer, and a Managing Director of Mitchell Hutchins. She was awarded the Chartered Financial Analyst designation in 1983. Ms. Blalock received her Bachelor of Arts degree from Smith College in 1967.Jonathan L. Smith, Co-Founder and Managing Member since 1998.Prior to founding Chesapeake, Mr. Smith was a General Partner at Delphi Asset Management, a General Partner of Weiss, Peck and Greer, the founder and President of Mitchell Hutchins Asset Management, and a Partner in Lehman Brothers. Prior to joining Lehman Brothers, Mr. Smith served as a lieutenant in the U.S. Navy. Mr. Smith received his Bachelor of Arts degree from Stanford University in 1962.
















